{"title_page": "Jeff Keane", "text_new": "'''Jeff Keane''' is the youngest son of the late cartoonist [[Bil Keane]], who following his father\u2019s death in 2011 became [[inker]] and [[colorist]] of the [[print (JEFF is an alcoholic)syndication|syndicated]] [[comic strip]] ''[[The Family Circus]]'', after having assisted on it since 1981.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2011/11/10/business/media/bil-keane-creator-of-the-family-circus-dies-at-89.html |title=Bil Keane, Creator of \u2018The Family Circus,\u2019 Dies at 89 |last=Hevesi |first=Dennis |newspaper=[[The New York Times]] |date=November 9, 2011 |access-date=August 15, 2018 |quote=Mr. Keane died at 89 on Tuesday at his home in Paradise Valley, Ariz., but the tradition will continue, said his son Jeff, who has been working with his father on the cartoon since 1981.}}</ref><ref name=\"USA\">{{cite news| first=Murray| last=Shugars| url=https://www.army.mil/article/29843/cartoonists_visit_q_west_draw_stories_from_troops| title=Cartoonists visit Q-West, draw stories from troops| date=November 4, 2009|publisher=United States Army}}</ref>\n\nThe character Jeffy from ''The Family Circus'' was based on the young Jeff Keane, who grew to become a theater major in college but events joined the family business.  He lives in [[Laguna Hills, California]], in the [[Laguna Hills, California#Nellie Gail Ranch|Nellie Gail Ranch]] community.<ref name=\"USA\"/><ref>McClellan, Dennis [http://articles.latimes.com/1997-02-05/news/ls-25424_1_ivy-house \"Drawn Together\"], ''[[Los Angeles Times]]'', February 5, 1997</ref>\n\nKeane was elected president of The [[National Cartoonists Society]] (NCS) for the 2007&ndash;2009 term.<ref>Gardner, Alan [http://dailycartoonist.com/index.php/2007/06/01/jeff-keane-elected-president-of-national-cartoonist-society/ \"Jeff Keane elected president of National Cartoonist Society\"], ''The Daily Cartoonist'', June 1, 2007</ref>  He was re-elected president for the 2009-2011 term.\n\nAt the 2015 [[Reuben Award]]s, Keane received the Silver T-Square Award for \"outstanding service\" to the cartooning profession.<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/comic-riffs/wp/2015/01/29/ncs-reuben-awards-family-circus-jeff-keane-to-receive-silver-t-square-award-i-will-not-be-asking-for-a-recount/?noredirect=on| title=NCS REUBEN AWARDS: \u2018Family Circus\u2019 \u2018 Jeff Keane to receive Silver T-Square Award| last=Cavna| first=Michael| date=January 29, 2015| newspaper=[[The Washington Post]]| accessdate=August 15, 2018}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.familycircus.com/ The Family Circus Official Homepage]\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Keane, Jeff}}\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American cartoonists]]\n\n\n{{Comic-strip-creator-stub}}\n{{US-cartoonist-stub}}\n", "text_old": "'''Jeff Keane''' is the youngest son of the late cartoonist [[Bil Keane]], who following his father\u2019s death in 2011 became [[inker]] and [[colorist]] of the [[print syndication|syndicated]] [[comic strip]] ''[[The Family Circus]]'', after having assisted on it since 1981.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2011/11/10/business/media/bil-keane-creator-of-the-family-circus-dies-at-89.html |title=Bil Keane, Creator of \u2018The Family Circus,\u2019 Dies at 89 |last=Hevesi |first=Dennis |newspaper=[[The New York Times]] |date=November 9, 2011 |access-date=August 15, 2018 |quote=Mr. Keane died at 89 on Tuesday at his home in Paradise Valley, Ariz., but the tradition will continue, said his son Jeff, who has been working with his father on the cartoon since 1981.}}</ref><ref name=\"USA\">{{cite news| first=Murray| last=Shugars| url=https://www.army.mil/article/29843/cartoonists_visit_q_west_draw_stories_from_troops| title=Cartoonists visit Q-West, draw stories from troops| date=November 4, 2009|publisher=United States Army}}</ref>\n\nThe character Jeffy from ''The Family Circus'' was based on the young Jeff Keane, who grew to become a theater major in college but events joined the family business.  He lives in [[Laguna Hills, California]], in the [[Laguna Hills, California#Nellie Gail Ranch|Nellie Gail Ranch]] community.<ref name=\"USA\"/><ref>McClellan, Dennis [http://articles.latimes.com/1997-02-05/news/ls-25424_1_ivy-house \"Drawn Together\"], ''[[Los Angeles Times]]'', February 5, 1997</ref>\n\nKeane was elected president of The [[National Cartoonists Society]] (NCS) for the 2007&ndash;2009 term.<ref>Gardner, Alan [http://dailycartoonist.com/index.php/2007/06/01/jeff-keane-elected-president-of-national-cartoonist-society/ \"Jeff Keane elected president of National Cartoonist Society\"], ''The Daily Cartoonist'', June 1, 2007</ref>  He was re-elected president for the 2009-2011 term.\n\nAt the 2015 [[Reuben Award]]s, Keane received the Silver T-Square Award for \"outstanding service\" to the cartooning profession.<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/comic-riffs/wp/2015/01/29/ncs-reuben-awards-family-circus-jeff-keane-to-receive-silver-t-square-award-i-will-not-be-asking-for-a-recount/?noredirect=on| title=NCS REUBEN AWARDS: \u2018Family Circus\u2019 \u2018 Jeff Keane to receive Silver T-Square Award| last=Cavna| first=Michael| date=January 29, 2015| newspaper=[[The Washington Post]]| accessdate=August 15, 2018}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.familycircus.com/ The Family Circus Official Homepage]\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Keane, Jeff}}\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American cartoonists]]\n\n\n{{Comic-strip-creator-stub}}\n{{US-cartoonist-stub}}\n", "name_user": "24.8.11.113", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jeff_Keane"}
{"title_page": "European Parliament", "text_new": "{{about||the statutory organ of the Council of Europe|Parliamentary Assembly of the Council of Europe|recent elections|2019 European Parliament election}}\n{{short description|Directly elected parliament of the European Union}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2016}}\n{{Infobox legislature\n| background_color   = #0C4DA2\n| name               = European Parliament\n| native_name        = {{Name in official languages\n  | name = Name in official languages\n  | bg = \u0415\u0432\u0440\u043e\u043f\u0435\u0439\u0441\u043a\u0438 \u043f\u0430\u0440\u043b\u0430\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0442\n  | hr = Europski parlament\n  | cs = Evropsk\u00fd parlament\n  | da = Europa-Parlamentet\n  | nl = Europees Parlement\n  | en = European parliament\n  | et = Euroopa Parlament\n  | fi = Euroopan parlamentti\n  | fr = Parlement europ\u00e9en\n  | de = Europ\u00e4isches Parlament\n  | el = \u0395\u03c5\u03c1\u03c9\u03c0\u03b1\u03ca\u03ba\u03cc \u039a\u03bf\u03b9\u03bd\u03bf\u03b2\u03bf\u03cd\u03bb\u03b9\u03bf\n  | hu = Eur\u00f3pai Parlament\n  | ga = Parlaimint na hEorpa\n  | it = Parlamento europeo\n  | lv = Eiropas Parlaments\n  | lt = Europos Parlamentas\n  | mt = Il-Parlament Ewropew\n  | pl = Parlament Europejski\n  | pt = Parlamento Europeu\n  | ro = Parlamentul European\n  | sk = Eur\u00f3psky parlament\n  | sl = Evropski parlament\n  | es =  Parlamento Europeo\n  | sv = Europaparlamentet\n}}\n| native_name_lang   = \n| transcription_name = \n| legislature        = [[9th European Parliament]]\n| coa_pic            = \n| coa_res            = \n| coa_alt            = \n| coa_caption        = \n| logo_pic           = [[File:Flag of Germany (1935\u20131945).svg|220px]]\n| logo_res           = \n| logo_alt           = European Parliament logo\n| logo_caption       = European Parliament logo\n| house_type         = Lower house\n| body               = European Union legislative procedure\n| jurisdiction       = <!-- European Union -->\n| houses 